(3) Genitive of the subject (corresponding to the subject of a verb):

hie est belli ludus. 10, 9. cupiditas principum. 10, 19. colloquia scurrarum. 42, 24.

(4) Genltive of the object (corresponding to the object of a verb):

certaminis spectatores. 29, 18. cura rei domesticae. 40, 12. vestri cultor. 26, 11.

Sometimes we can only decide from the context whether a. genitive is subjective or obiective.

Many verbs and adjectives take an objectiva genitive, e.g. those denoting clevill, fumeae, want, and various kinds of

feelinys.

nos sodalicii non paenitet. 4, 7. me taedet tam prolixi. 21, 26. spectaculorum perspicaces. 24, 17. librorum plena sunt omnia. 38, 6. laboris patiens. 16, 12.

discendi cupidus. 12, 21. perparcus temporis. 45, 24.
